    <div style="margin-top:12px;">
        <strong>Features:</strong>
        <ul style="margin:4px 0 0;padding-left:18px;">
            <li><strong>Hit Counter</strong> &mdash; Tracks how many times each redirect was triggered</li>
            <li><strong>Scheduling</strong> &mdash; Set Active From / Active Until dates for time-limited redirects</li>
            <li><strong>404 Logging</strong> &mdash; All 404 errors are automatically logged with hit counts, timestamps, and referer URLs</li>
            <li><strong>Import/Export CSV</strong> &mdash; Bulk manage redirects via CSV files</li>
            <li><strong>Priority</strong> &mdash; Lower number = checked first. If multiple patterns match, the highest-priority redirect wins</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <p style="margin:8px 0 0;color:#555;">
        <strong>Best Practice:</strong> Use 301 for permanent moves (product discontinuation, URL restructuring).
        Use 302 only for temporary situations (seasonal promotions, A/B testing).
        Avoid redirect chains (A &rarr; B &rarr; C) &mdash; always redirect directly to the final URL.
    </p>
